    "original": " bellows like a startled buffalo as he falls out of the sky, landing with a wince-inducing crump in the snow. He lies there unmoving for several moments, long enough for you to start thinking he’s done for the day. Then he claws himself back to his hoofs, wild rage in his eyes. Tentacles and tail swinging, he lets out a terrible, primordial war-cry that reverberates off the frozen hills and charges at you, throwing aside his weapons to strike at you with fists like barbells. ",
